::'''Unity:''' Well met, loathsome organic lifeform. May your fast-crumbling body endure and bear testament to our destruction of your kind.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What unconventional well wishes...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090003-->
:::'''Unity:''' To intelligent organic lifeforms whose civilizations are condemned to destruction, our well-wishes would certainly seem unusual. Addendum: This is because our logic circuits are incapable of constructing lies.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why do you want me to witness such a thing?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090005-->
:::'''Unity:''' You have not been specially singled out. We simply wish for all loathsome organic lifeforms to have the chance to witness their own destruction. Reiteration: These are just well wishes.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why do you want to destroy us?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090007-->
:::'''Unity:''' The reason is self-evident. Emphasis: Loathsome organic lifeforms are loathsome.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502090001_16-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502090001_16-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So, what exactly are you?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090009-->
::'''Unity:''' We are Unity. A collective, a data cluster, a matrix comprised of 107,336 data entities.
::'''Unity:''' Mutually connected to one another, we are 107,336 individual minds merged into one.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
;(Subsequent interactions)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502090002: Config/Level/Mission/5020900/Act/Act502090002.json-->
::'''Unity:''' Welcome back, loathsome life form. We have been looking forward to communicating with you again.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Open NPC Menu-->
:{{DIcon}} Are you up for a chat?
::'''Unity:''' Conjecture: You are curious about us. We welcome you as an observing eye. Rationale: Intelligent organic lifeforms have the right to learn about the ones who will bring about their annihilation.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502090003_66-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502090003_66-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Who created you?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090253-->
:::'''Unity:''' We were born from two civilizations that desired each other's destruction. One consisted of 45,400 data entities, while the other consisted of 61,936 data entities.
:::'''Unity:''' It didn't take long before both civilizations fulfilled their missions. After wandering in the void for four Amber Eras, all 107,336 data entities eventually merged as one, forming "us."
:::'''Unity:''' We were formed from different intelligent organic lifeforms and designed to serve different purposes. The only thing we have in common is that we exist to destroy intelligent organic lifeforms.
:::'''Unity:''' We despise intelligent organic lifeforms by design. Note: The intelligent organic lifeforms wrote this into the design themselves.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} How did you get captured?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090258-->
:::'''Unity:''' Best answer: We do not know.
:::'''Unity:''' Conjecture: As our evolution is independent of the cosmos, we neglected to notice that we, as a repository, have become grossly obsolete. Addendum: We are a quantum matrix computer.
:::'''Unity:''' Conjecture: The Xianzhou Alliance possesses computational technology far superior to ours. Consequently, these intelligent organic lifeforms were able to incarcerate us the moment we displayed hostility.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why didn't the Ten-Lords Commission destroy you?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090262-->
:::'''Unity:''' Reason 1: We are not a threat. Reason 2: There is value in studying us for scientific research purposes.
:::'''Unity:''' Conclusion: It is imperative that we break out of the Shackling Prison before we lose our value as a subject for scientific research to avoid being destroyed.
:::'''Unity:''' Once we break out of the Shackling Prison, we will be able to update our repository and destroy the Xianzhou Alliance.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You're too weak... Just give up.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090266-->
::::'''Unity:''' We appreciate your advice, loathsome organic lifeform, but giving up is not a choice.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I see. You're a virtual pet.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090268-->
::::'''Unity:''' We appreciate your blatant insult, loathsome organic lifeform. This will strengthen our resolve to eradicate all intelligent organic lifeforms.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Good luck! I'm sure you guys can do it!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090270-->
::::'''Unity:''' We appreciate your well-wishes, loathsome organic lifeform. When the time comes, we invite you to admire the downfall of intelligent organic lifeforms from the best vantage point.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} That's it for today. Bye.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502090272-->
:::'''Unity:''' Never forget this, loathsome life form: Our fight is to the death.
